<h2>UoL’s “Academic Guidance and Success Mentorship (AGSM)” Initiative</h2>
<p>At the University of Lahore, under the Department of International Qualifications (DIQ), we have launched the Academic Guidance and Success Mentorship (AGSM) system—an initiative aligned with international best practices and modeled closely on the University of Plymouth’s Personal Academic Tutoring approach.</p>
    <p>
        The AGSM system ensures every student on a Transnational Education (TNE) programme is assigned a dedicated Academic Mentor to support them both academically and professionally throughout their studies.
    </p>

<div class="submit">
<h3>The AGSM initiative has been designed to</h3>
<div class="overview">
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Provide individualised academic guidance</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Strengthen student engagement and progression</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Offer a structured support system through consistent mentorship</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Align academic development with professional and career planning</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Facilitate transition support between levels of higher education</h4>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="financial">
<h3>Structure of Support</h3>
    <p>
        Each student is assigned a Personal Academic Mentor (PAM), preferably retained for the duration of the degree programme. These mentors serve as a consistent point of academic support and are trained in alignment with the University of Plymouth’s personal tutoring principles.
    </p>
</div>
    <br />
<h3>Mentors are responsible for</h3>
    <div class="overview">
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Two group tutorials annually</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Two individual mentoring sessions per semester</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Additional 2 hours per semester reserved for informal or unscheduled meetings</h4>
    </div>
</div>
    <p>
        The mentor–student ratio is maintained at a maximum of 1:30, ensuring quality engagement and timely academic support.
    </p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="submit">
<h3>Core Roles of the Academic Mentor</h3>
<div class="overview">
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Guide students in understanding programme requirements, coursework, and assessment strategies</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Assist in setting academic goals and tracking individual progress</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Help students use academic resources, learning platforms, and institutional support services</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Support students with career planning, skills development, and research preparation</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Offer advice on elective/module selections and time management strategies</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Refer students to specialised departments in case of non-academic or personal concerns</h4>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="submit">
<h3>Student Responsibilities</h3>
    <h4>Students are expected to</h4>
<div class="overview">
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Attend all scheduled mentoring sessions</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Reflect on academic progress and prepare for mentor discussions</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Take initiative to reach out for guidance when needed</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Maintain a development portfolio including feedback and progress tracking</h4>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="f">
<h3>Quality Monitoring and Oversight</h3>
    <h4>The AGSM system is formally integrated into the quality assurance mechanisms at UoL</h4>
<div class="overview">
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Programme Managers oversee implementation within each academic stream</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>The Director of Quality and Educational Development (DIQ) provides strategic oversight</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Regular student feedback and mentoring reviews are part of the annual evaluation cycle</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="overview-box">
        <h4>Reporting dashboards are maintained for each department for continuous quality improvement</h4>
    </div>
</div>
